    "en": "The imperative is used to give commands or requests. At A1 level, basic verbs are introduced.\n\n<strong>1. Du form</strong>\nVerb stem (without du)\n- Komm! (Come!)\n- Mach die Tür auf! (Open the door!)\n\n<strong>2. Ihr form</strong>\nVerb + ihr\n- Kommt! (Come! plural)\n- Macht die Hausaufgaben! (Do the homework!)\n\n<strong>3. Sie form (formal)</strong>\nVerb + Sie + object\n- Kommen Sie bitte! (Please come!)\n- Machen Sie das Fenster auf! (Open the window!)\n\n<strong>4. Negative Commands</strong>\nNicht + verb\n- Geh nicht weg! (Don’t go!)\n- Esst das nicht! (Don’t eat that!)\n\n<strong>5. Summary</strong>\nImperative is important for giving direct commands in daily conversation.",
    
